---
description: Lightweight safety checks for edits
alwaysApply: true
---

Keep changes safe and reviewable:
- Prefer small, localized diffs over broad refactors.
- Preserve existing file discovery behavior unless explicitly requested (stage files are discovered from the current working directory).
- Avoid changing gameplay timing/logic “to clean up” unless there is a user-visible bug or requirement.

When editing:
- If touching `Board::load`, `.screen` parsing, or board symbols, update `MEMORY_BANK.md` accordingly.
- If touching controls, movement rules, jumping/falling rules, hammer, or extra-life behavior, update `MEMORY_BANK.md` accordingly.

Verification checklist (quick):
- Game still builds in Visual Studio.
- At least one `dkong*.screen` loads when the working directory contains stage files.
- Basic inputs still work: `w/a/s/d` movement, `p` hammer use.

